{
  "texts": [
    "It is also possible that SEE annotation would not generalize well, or suffer from more disagreements in other languages, though we believe this is unlikely.",
    "A further limitation in terms of the evaluation of pretrained LLMs is that we cannot rule out that models have seen some of the evaluation data in some form during pretraining.",
    "GUM data is part of the Universal Dependencies project, which is managed over GitHub, and is therefore susceptible to inclusion in the Pile dataset, known to be used as training data for GPT models.",
    "If such effects are present in our evaluation, they should minimize, rather than maximize the contribution of providing SEE information.",
    "Our data is also relatively small in terms of summarization datasets, meaning that while it may not substantially affect LLM training, more data would lead to better results."
  ]
}